result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
3:19 p.m.  State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present, in custody, with Attorney Timothy Hogan.

Atty Hogan states 2014CF90 is to be DRI.  ADA concurs.  2014TR1369 - ADA moves to dismiss.

ADA recites agreement - defendant plea to count 1 on 2014CF37 - dismiss the repeater.  DRI count 2 on 2014CF37.  Requests a Presentence Investigation.  Attorney Hogan concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to count 1.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  ADA confirms compliance with any victim/witness rights.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 on 2014CF37 - strikes the repeater.  Court DRI count 2.  Court dismisses 2014TR1369.  Court DRI 2014CF90.  Court orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Court orders a Presentece Report to be completed within 60 days - sentencing to be held thereafter.

Court adjourned at 3:27 p.m.
Plea/sentencing hearing on October 28, 2014 at 03:00 pm.

3:35 p.m.  State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present with Attorney Timothy Hogan (2014CF37 only).

Statement by Attorney Hogan - believes he will be appointed on 2014CF90 as well.

2014CF37
Statement by Attorney Hogan - requests a plea hearing date.

Court directs Plea/Sentencing to be held on both cases to be held in thirty to sixty days.

Court adjourned at 3:36 p.m.
Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.
Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.

2:52 p.m.  State by DA Andrew Christenson.  Defendant present, in custody and via video from Green Lake County Jail, with Attorney Barb Privat.

Attorney Privat confirms receipt of the complaint - waives reading.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court finds probable cause.

Court orders bond set at $500.00 Signature Bond. with the conditions of:  Complete processing if defendant has not already done so.

Attorney Privat waives time limits as to Preliminary - states the defendant qualifies for Public Defender representation.

Court directs matter be held the next time Attorney Hoag is present (tomorrow).

Court adjourned at 2:54 p.m.
